messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /printshops/{id}/pricetable/covers

All methods acceptable: false

Allowed methods (based on the code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: true
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In PriceTableController.editCoverItem the method is annotated with:
  @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/covers", method = RequestMethod.PUT)
  This explicitly sets the endpoint path to "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/covers" and restricts the handler to the HTTP PUT method.
- Because the RequestMapping explicitly specifies PUT, no other HTTP methods are declared for this handler in the code. Following the instruction to base acceptability solely on the code (not on framework behavior), only PUT is marked true and all other methods are false.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would change the path prefix in the provided file, so the full path is exactly the value in the method-level annotation.
